The African National Congress (ANC) says it has full confidence in President Cyril Ramaphosa‘s efforts to build a united South Africa and continues to back the leader’s commitment to fighting corruption. The governing party was responding to the Public Protector’s report on the Bosasa matter. Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane found that President Ramaphosa had misled Parliament about the Bosasa donation to his ANC presidential campaign. She has called on the NPA to probe the matter as well as Parliament’s ethics committee to look into the issue. However, Ramaphosa says the Public Protector has made errors in fact and in law. He released his 88 page response to her June preliminary report, in which Ramaphosa says Mkhwebane largely ignored in compiling her final report. President Ramaphosa’s response below:  Related video click below: